@node "introduction" "Handy - Introduction"

 Handy is an Atari Lynx emulator written by Keith Wilkins.

@endnode

@node "requirements" "Handy - Requirements"

 Hardware:

  * Amiga with a PowerPC board
  * AGA or CGFX
  * 16 MB of RAM
  * OS 3.0

 Software:

  * WarpUP v4.0
  * lynxboot.img (I will NOT send it to you)

@endnode

@node "features" "Handy - Features"

 This Atari Lynx emulator is quite compatible and most ROMs should
 work flawlessly.

@endnode

@node "installation" "Handy - Installation"

 Just copy it to any place on your HD.

@endnode

@node "usage" "Handy - Usage"

 * Starting Handy:

  1. Place the lynxboot.img file in the same directory as Handy
  2. Open a shell window
  3. Increase the stack, 100k (stack 100000 <ENTER>) should be enough
  4. Type Handy.exe <OPTIONS> <ENTER>

 * Keyboard keys:

  ESC   - Quit
  A     - Button A
  S     - Button B
  Q     - Button Opt1
  W     - Button Opt2
  ENTER - Pause
  Arrow keys - Left, Right, Up, Down

 * CD32 pad buttons:

  Green  - Button Opt1
  Yellow - Button OPt2
  Red    - Button A
  Blue   - Button B
  Start  - Pause
  Directional buttons - Left, Right, Up, Down

@endnode

@node "options" "Handy - Options"

 REQUESTER/S   : use screenmode requester (def: CGFX BestModeID/PAL Lores).
 JOYPAD/S      : CD32 joypad (def: keyboard).
 CGFX/S        : CGFX instead of direct gfxmem access (def: off).
 SOUND/S       : sound (def: off).
 SCREENMODE/N  : use the specified screenmode (def: CGFX BestModeID/PAL Lores).
 NOSTALGIA/S   : save the screenshot in Nostalgia:samples/ (def: current directory).

@endnode

